Task 1: Tilt Detection with LED Indicator
Instructions:

Connect an LED to digital pin D9.
Modify the code so that:
The LED turns ON when the sensor detects a tilt.
The LED remains OFF when no tilt is detected.
Print the sensor state in the serial monitor.

Task 2: Tilt Alert with Buzzer
Instructions:

Connect a buzzer to digital pin D10.
Modify the code so that:
The buzzer sounds when the sensor detects a tilt.
The buzzer remains silent when no tilt is detected.
Keep the LED functionality from Task 1.

Task 3: Counting Tilt Events
Instructions:

Create a variable to store the tilt count.
Each time a tilt is detected, increment the count.
Display the updated count on the serial monitor.
